parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake system can cause the brakes to lock up without warning, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brakes suddenly become inoperable
the brake system locks without warning
the motorcycle goes into a tailspin
the brake fluid level is low without evidence of a leak
a loud popping noise is heard from the rear of the bike.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A leak in the combined brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake fluid level is low
brake system failure
inability to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Wiring Inside Brake System Block
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor wiring inside the brake system block can cause electrical failures, leading to brake system malfunctions and potential accidents.
symptoms: Brake system failure
electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel bearing can cause the wheel to seize, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear wheel bearing feels rough
the rear wheel bearing is fractured
the rear wheel bearing needs to be replaced
the rear wheel seizes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire blistering can lead to sudden tire failure, loss of control, and accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Blisters or bubbles on the tire surface
typically along the center line or sidewall
which can be visible to the naked eye.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wobble on deceleration can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel wobbles or vibrates when decelerating from 45-30 mph
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when slowing down
the steering wheel feels unstable or loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper shifting of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle does not shift properly
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or stalls
difficulty shifting into gear
unusual noises or vibrations when shifting.
